5:
Oh, oh, Stella, what's that store over
there?
9:
It's a weapons shop. They sell things
like swords.
13:
Swords? You mean those hideous
metal sticks that are incredibly
inefficient at disposing of your foes?
18:
What did I say about being rude?
Especially in public!
21:
What? Am I wrong? Oh, but I guess a
meathead who punches things like
you wouldn't get it.
25:
You little... Ugh, how come you're so
nice to Stella and only her?
29:
Just look at her. Could you even be
mean to her if you tried?
32: Huh... Yeah, no, you got a point.
40:
Oh, it's you! I didn't know you were in
town!
43:
Hey there, kid. Been a while. How're
you doing?
48:
Whaaat? Mama, I know the comics
you've been reading. 2D is one thing,
but 3D?
52:
Huh? Have you been spying on my
data?!
55:
Also, you're totally painting the
wrong picture here! The comics I
read are all wholesome!
59:
Did I say they weren't? Mama, you're
the one suggesting that, you know.
65:
And? What's it to you? She's my
mama, not yours.
69:
You really need to stop picking
fights with literally everyone you run
into.
76:
...So after saving this child, you
promised to teach him magic so he
could prove he's better than his
bullies.
79:
Do you have any brain cells left in
your noggin? How do you expect to
teach him magic when you can't
use it?
83:
Urk... L-listen, I'm getting advice from
mages who know what they're
doing!
87:
Uh-huh. I don't see why you're even
bothering in the first place. It's stupid
to try and play fair with people that
break the rules.
91:
Are you listening to me? You better
be.
95:
Can't believe you're lecturing me...
You really take after Themis in that
regard, ugh.
98:
...I want to show them they're wrong
about me. I don't want to rely on
other people forever.
102:
You say that, but you're asking
someone else to teach you magic.
105:
Ngh... I-I'm still the one doing the
studying! I'm working hard at it too!
109:
So what? Has hard work gotten you
what you wanted?
113:
You think just doing your best will
earn you an escape out of hell? As if!
117:
I know someone who tried to do
exactly that, and all she managed
to do was contradict herself and
make mistakes at every turn.
126:
If you're not doing fine, then tell
someone! Don't keep it bottled up
inside!
129: If you came to me, I'd
133: Stinelle, you want to help, don't you?
139:
Why would I have the desire to help?
I'm going to become a god.
143:
Once I do, I'll create the perfect
world, where sinners are properly
punished, and everyone can live
happily together.
146:
...Nothing else should matter but
making sure justice is doled out
properly.
154:
You know, I'm not against your end
goal. I just wish you went about it a
different way.
162:
It's easy to forget when you're a
hero, but... Most people are pretty
happy living their lives without
worrying about what's right or
wrong.
164:
They just wanna eat good food,
read fun comics... Try out new things
that they never got to do before.
168: ...Is that what humanity is to you?
170:
Despite their capacity to hurt others
and themselves...
172: You think they're still worth saving?
179:
Why don't you join me and give the
hero thing a try?
181:
Can't hurt to learn a thing or two
about helping others if you wanna
become the god that'll save us all.
186:
...Hmph, fine. I'll indulge your
stupidity for today.
190:
Though I'm not sure how much help
I'll be. It's not like I'm from a world
with magic either
194:
...Wait. Is this it? Are you telling me
you don't understand this material?
200:
Magic's like a compiler that
executes commands in worlds
supporting the language.
203:
Of course, you probably need to be
equipped with the right circuitry to
get it to work. If I attempted these
incantations, I don't think they'd do
much but be empty words.
207:
...I'm sorry, what? Huh? I'm totally lost
here.
211:
I find it hilarious that a zero-year-old
child figured this out before you did.
216: Okay, that's enough out of you!
222:
Thanks for today, Nate! You too,
Stinelle!
225:
What'd you think? It's nice to do
something other than beating up
bad guys for once, right?
229:
...It wasn't awful, I guess. I'll give you
that much.
243:
Pffft, hahaha! Well, Stella... Guess
you got on her bad side for once.
253:
As punishment, you have to hold my
hand the whole way back!
